description:
&lt;h1&gt;Bank Registered Nursing Staff&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staffing Solutions provide motivated, reliable staff to cover temporary vacancies or shortfalls at the Royal United Hospitals Bath NHS Foundation Trust (RUH). &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The bank team are currently recruiting Nurses, RMNs for inpatient areas, Paediatric staff and Theatre Practitioners.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;NURSES/RMNs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The RUH is an acute hospital and our Bank staff are in-demand across wards and out-patient areas. For registered mental health nurses, the demand is with 1-1 support of patients throughout various wards as and when required, dealing with patients who have challenging behaviours.&lt;br /&gt; We are currently looking for both General Nurses and Mental Health Nurses to join our team. You will work in various locations throughout the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;These shifts include:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Early shifts: 0700 -1300 or 0730-1330&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Late shifts: 1400-2000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Long days: 0700-1930 or 0730-2000&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Night shifts: 1900-0730 or 1930-0800&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;You will have to be qualified with the appropriate NMC registration and have relevant acute hospital nursing experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat please contact &lt;strong&gt;Clychelle Mann, Bank Nurse Development Facilitator on 01225 825377.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;THEATRES&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for Operating Department Practitioners, Scrub Nurses and Anaesthetic Assistants with &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;a minimum of 6 months experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; in the Operating Theatre Department to join our bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are able to offer excellent development opportunities in specialties including General Surgery, ENT, Orthopaedics, Trauma, Gynaecology, Urology and Obstetrics. We have regular and occasional work to suit your needs and can offer flexible working patterns – Shifts will be generally 8-6 Monday to Friday with the possibility of working unsocial, nights and weekends depending on experience– so you can work around other commitments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a new bank member we will also provide you with up to 4 supervised shifts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal chat please telephone &lt;strong&gt;Theatre Recruitment Lead Milla Kivela, on 01225 825703 or Bleep 7045, Clychelle Mann, Bank Nurse Development Facilitator on 01225 825377.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BENEFITS FOR ALL BANK STAFF:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS benefits including pension, holiday pay and discounts in high street stores and online**.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working patterns to meet your needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competitive rates of pay, including RRP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Unsociable hours pay.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training and updates (we’ll pay for all mandatory training updates).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support from the Bank Nurse Facilitator and Band 6 Pool staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid Orientation shifts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Online shift-booking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A fully paid Trust Induction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A passport system for mandatory training, meaning we accept updates from other NHS providers who are registered with the Core Skills framework.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Free uniforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A free DBS check.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to experience life in other departments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Regular extra work or occasional shifts to fit around other commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A way to keep up to date with your acute nursing skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Trust will act as your confirmer in the revalidation process and if you’re a regular Bank-only worker, you’ll have the chance to attend revalidation workshops.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;** Valid in certain stores and online shops with a valid NHS ID and/or Blue Light card&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;We pay all band 5 staff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASIC HRS=-£15.66&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ANNUAL SALARY= £30,615&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLUS A/L= £17.55&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLUS 20.07% (A/L+RRP) =£18.80&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UNSOCIAL/SAT/NIGHT 30% = £24.44&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SUN/BH 60% =£30.08&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We a pay an enhanced rate for shifts booked in ED and MAU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
